    <br />
    <br />
    <b>To plan for developmental programmes for the benefit of faculty and students of the affiliated college system by :</b>
    <ul class="special_list">
        <li>Sharing of best practices among the stakeholders.</li>
        <li>Developing teaching-learning materials for theory and lab courses and placing on JNTUH website with access to all.</li>
        <li>Conducting seminars and workshops on pedagogy to help new teachers in urban/rural areas.</li>
        <li>Conducting remedial courses in English for students in urban/rural areas.</li>
        <li>Conducting Faculty Development Programmes for in service teachers in urban/rural areas.</li>
        <li>Sharing of Expertise, Learning Materials, Journals, Books, etc</li>
        <li>Arranging seminars/lectures in urban/ rural colleges.</li>
        <li>Undertaking joint research programmes between JNTUH and affiliated colleges.</li>
        <li>Try and generate a corpus fund to grant Rs. 1 lakh to faculty members desirous of pursuing Ph.D.in JNTUH.</li>
        <li>Interaction with Industry for undertaking meaningful and practical projects.</li>
        <li>Formation of professional societies such as ISTE, IEEE, ISHRAE, etc.</li>
        <li>Holding design competitions, business plan competitions in urban/rural areas.</li>
        <li>Holding open houses showcasing UG and PG projects for idea generation.</li>
        <li>Formation of Hobby Clubs (Robotics club, etc) for hands on experiential learning.</li>
        <li>Channelize the youth energies into constructive activities such as Sports, NSS, Yoga, etc.</li>
    </ul>
